What is CSS?
  CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) is a stylesheet language used to style and design HTML web pages. It controls the appearance of elements, including colors, fonts, spacing, layouts, and responsiveness.

Features
  - Styles and enhances web pages
  - Separates design from content
  - Supports responsive web design
  - Provides animations and transitions
  - Reusable and maintainable styles
  - Cross-browser compatibility

Components
  - Selectors
  - Properties
  - Values
  - Declarations
  - Rulesets
  - Media Queries

Advantages
  - Improves the visual appearance of web pages
  - Reduces code repetition
  - Easy to maintain and update
  - Faster page loading with external stylesheets
  - Supports responsive layouts
  - Enhances user experience
  - Works seamlessly with HTML and JavaScript
  
